{"questionId":"9074752","questionHtml":"<p>A ray of light enters from air into a water droplet of radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> at point S. S is a vertical distance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> from the centre of the droplet. The droplet has a refractive index <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> and the angle of refraction is <em>θ</em>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/35ad586014203e57e0962e53cb6c975dc6da5ef4.png\">What is sin <em>θ</em>?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></math></em></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>r</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow><mi>h</mi></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074752","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.14","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A ray of light enters from air into a water droplet of radius r at point S. S is a vertical distance h from the centre of the droplet. The droplet has a refractive index n and the ","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"14","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Waves","4.4 – Wave behaviour","Core","Topic 4: Waves"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}